# Config & Secrets

- Repo must use placeholder API key: `YOUR_GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY_HERE`
- Never log passwords or full API keys
- Per-account fields: `enabled`, `username`, `loginMethod` (`credentials` | `manual`), `sourceMode` (`new_post_added_to_account` | `url_list` | `hashtag_list` | `hashtag_api`), `skillsFile` (required when enabled), optional `password` (required for `credentials`), `targets` (monitor mode), `postUrlsFile` (url_list), `hashtags` array (hashtag_list / hashtag_api), `hashtagSearch` (`ui_search` / `api_search`), `instagramApiAccessToken` + `instagramApiUserId` (hashtag_api), `aiPromptHint`, `actionDelaySeconds`
- Set `developerMode: true` only for local debugging; keep `headless: false` for check-accounts
- Cookie files live at `data/cookies/{username}.json` — never commit them

```typescript
// BAD — real credentials in committed config
googleAiApiKey: "AIzaSy...",
password: "myRealPassword123",

// GOOD — placeholders; user fills locally
googleAiApiKey: "YOUR_GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY_HERE",
password: "YOUR_PASSWORD_HERE",
instagramApiAccessToken: "YOUR_INSTAGRAM_API_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE",
instagramApiUserId: "YOUR_INSTAGRAM_API_USER_ID_HERE",
```
